  "reasoning_summary": "For primary earners in the lowest earnings decile, labor supply tends to be relatively responsive on the intensive margin compared to higher deciles, because low-wage workers are closer to a participation margin and face binding budget constraints. However, the elasticity is still bounded: most estimates for low-skilled or low-wage workers' labor supply elasticity sit in the 0.05–0.25 range, with central tendency around 0.1. Uncertainty about whether decile 1 contains many constrained workers (driving the elasticity higher) versus many workers with very limited hours flexibility (pulling it lower) motivates a fairly wide 90% interval."
}

